@taenacity_translations Most commonly, authors will draw their stories completely uncensored, then apply whatever censorship is required by their publisher at the end. If it's a magazine chapter, the author might release a less censored version later in a book. 

This author has released "uncensored" versions of their stories through Fakku which were still whited-out because the author never bothered to draw the genitals in the first place, and therefore had no uncensored version to provide. 

It got to the point where I wondered if the author never bothered to learn how to draw genitals, or if it was a stylistic choice. I'm glad that doesn't seem to be the case.
